Hexagonal architecture assumes that the business logic is in the center of the architecture and all the interactions with the data stores, clients, and other systems are equal. There is a contract between the business logic and every nonbusiness logic component, but there is no distinction between the layers above and below.Hexagonal architecture assumes that the business logic is in the center of the architecture and all the interactions with the data stores, clients, and other systems are equal. There is a contract between the business logic and every nonbusiness logic component, but there is no distinction between the layers above and below.
